 in terms of the\nusual $n_s$ and $r$ parameters, given that the parameterisation used here\nincludes, implicitly, a running spectral index.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 May 2014 10:35:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-24"}
